For the first primary outcome, i.e. the mortality outcome, period prevalence of death will be compared between the randomly assigned treatment groups using relative risk regression. Mortality (a binary variable) will be defined as any event of death from time of randomisation to end of day 180. Participants with a missing mortality outcome will be assigned ‘alive’. For the primary ITT analysis, the following model will be used:
